  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nMy mainnet node seems to be working fine, but calling `eth.getBlock('latest')` returns an old block\r\n![nethermind](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67484816/183644078-ccead17b-5329-4a39-aee2-cd67ccaaf069.png)\r\n\r\nLooking through the logs around block `15304812` nethermind complained that:\r\n\r\n`2022-08-09 02:02:22.8626|100% of nodes did not respond to a Ping message - 50/50`\r\n\r\n(which is strange, because none of the other nodes on the same machine did have a problem at the time)\r\nand then started syncing.\r\n\r\nIt synced up to `15304812` but then continued onwards from `15304815`. `15304813` and `15304814` do not appear in the logs \r\n[nethermind.log](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/9290233/nethermind.log)\r\n\r\nStart Command:\r\n```\r\ndotnet run -c Release -- --config mainnet     \\\r\n--datadir=/node/mainnet/nethermind_data       \\\r\n--JsonRpc.Enabled=true                        \\\r\n--Sync.SnapSync=true                          \\\r\n--Network.P2PPort=10301                       \\\r\n--Network.DiscoveryPort=10301                 \\\r\n--JsonRpc.Port=10303                          \\\r\n--Network.ActivePeersMaxCount=50              \\\r\n--JsonRpc.Host=127.0.0.1            \r\n```          \r\n\r\nVersion: `7b5b14f3534396e14c5bf6eb2be6a63b34c01007`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
